<br>
I also play a level 50 Paladin, and you know something?  The damage output for the Paladin is exactly the same for my Zerk.  There's something wrong with this picture, for several reasons:<br>
<br>
1)  My Zerk's Strength is 200 with all my equipment on.  My Paladin's strength is 172.<br>
<br>
2)  Zerkers are a pure tank, Paladins are a hybrid.  Therefore, melee damage output should be higher because that is the definition of the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>pure tank.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
3)  The Paladin is specced 43 slash and 42 shield.  The Zerk is specced 50 Left Axe 48 Axe.<br>
<br>
4)  While both characters are using a 16.5 dps weapon, my Zerk has a much better spellcrafting template.<br>
<br>
5)  Plate armor.<br>
<br>
6)  Chants.<br>
<br>
7)  Self end-regen on the Paladin character.<br>
<br>
What you don't get is the fact that I had always thought Mercs and Blademasters should get some loving.  For the same reasons as I listed above, Mercs should do more damage than Paladins.  The fact that they don't is retarted.<br>
<br>
Instead of being smug about an overcompensated knee-jerk implementation of a lame attempt at class/realm balance, you should be upset along with the Zerkers.  Why?  Simple:<br>
<br>
If they don't let up a little bit on the 30-60% damage reduction, Blademasters and Mercenaries will <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>never</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> see any kind of boost in damage output.<br>
<br>
